This paper discusses the emerging field of fair machine learning, which is closely related to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also touches upon the ethical and societal implications of machine learning, which could fall under the sub-categories of cyber ethics (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the different interpretations of democracy embedded in our culture, which could be related to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
